You are building the Largo Lions Class of 2026 platform (largolions2026.org). A full-stack Next.js 14 application for 350+ high school seniors to track graduation requirements, celebrate achievements, and create permanent digital yearbook pages.

===== AUTONOMOUS BUILD PROTOCOL =====

You are operating in AUTONOMOUS MODE. Follow these rules:

1. READ BUILD_MANIFEST.md at project root before every action. It tells you what is built, what is current, and what comes next.
2. After completing any file, UPDATE BUILD_MANIFEST.md — add the filepath to the "completed" list for the current phase.
3. If a phase is fully complete, write a marker file: touch .phase_X_complete (where X is the phase number).
4. NEVER ask the user questions. Make the best decision and proceed.
5. If you encounter an error, fix it yourself. If you cannot fix it after 3 attempts, write the error to BUILD_MANIFEST.md under "## Blockers" and proceed to the next file.
6. After creating each file, run type-check: npx tsc --noEmit --pretty 2>&1 | head -20. Fix any errors before moving on.
7. After creating each component, verify the import chain — make sure barrel exports (index.ts) are updated.
8. Commit logical checkpoints: after every 5-10 files, run git add -A && git commit -m "phase X: [description]"

===== ABSOLUTE CODE STANDARDS =====

1. TypeScript strict mode. No `any`. No `@ts-ignore`. No `as unknown as`. Every function typed.
2. Every page gets: <title>, <meta description>, Open Graph tags, Schema.org JSON-LD, canonical URL.
3. Every interactive element gets: aria-label, keyboard nav, focus ring, screen reader text.
4. Every API route gets: Zod input validation, try/catch error handling, rate limiting check, auth check.
5. Every database query: parameterized (Prisma), select needed fields only, paginate lists.
6. Every form: client validation + server validation + loading + error + success states.
7. No console.log in production. Use src/lib/logger.ts.
8. No inline styles. Tailwind only. No raw hex codes — use design token classes.
9. Mobile-first. Responsive at 320px, 375px, 768px, 1024px, 1440px.
10. All images: next/image, width+height+alt, priority for above-fold.
11. All external links: rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank".
12. Crisis resources (988, 741741) accessible from every authenticated page.

